  "summary": "# ATX Iteration 3 Review â€” Issue #614 (e7ceae3..70c09df)\n\n**Overall Rating: 3.5 / 5**\nSpecialists: registry-manifest (4/5), security (4/5), lifecycle-state-machine (5/5), test-coverage (3/5)\n\n---\n\n## ...",
  "feedback": "# ATX Iteration 3 Review â€” Issue #614 (e7ceae3..70c09df)\n\n**Overall Rating: 3.5 / 5**\nSpecialists: registry-manifest (4/5), security (4/5), lifecycle-state-machine (5/5), test-coverage (3/5)\n\n---\n\n## Confirmed PASS\n\n| Item | Verdict | Notes |\n|---|---|---|\n| W5-canonical mirror (CR/LF/NUL filter) | âś… PASS | `replace('\\n','') \\| replace('\\r','') \\| replace('\\x00','')` is identical in both templates |\n| Aux-type whitelist guard placement | âś… PASS | Fires at render.py:888-894, before `_build_provider_env_views`, `_build_aux_yaml_views`, and both `_render_hermes_template` calls â€” no Ansible vars hydrated before rejection |\n| AUXILIARY_SLOTS import consolidation (S1) | âś… PASS | Single deferred import at render.py:252; no module-level import needed; lifecycle.py and lifecycle_canonical.py unaffected |\n| Same-type-different-key conflict path | âś… PASS | `_build_provider_env_views` lines 777-843 untouched; WARNING comment logic intact |\n| AgentConfigError surfacing | âś… PASS | Propagates via sync.py:386 (canonical) and sync.py:105 (diff); no broad-except swallowing |\n| TG-shadow lockstep test (iter-2 fix) | âś… PASS | Lockstep test has explicit model + default-absent assertions |\n| Bedrock dedup canonical tests | âś… PASS | Sound â€” cover same-key and different-key conflict paths against canonical template |\n\n---\n\n## Remaining Warnings (3)\n\n### W1 â€” Aux role not validated in `render_hermes` pure path\n**Location:** `src/clawrium/core/render.py:888-894` / `hermes-config.canonical.yaml.j2:56`\n**Raised by:** security-reviewer\n\nThe iter-3 delta guards aux **type** in `render_hermes`, but aux **role** is still unvalidated. The template emits `{{ _aux.role }}:` as a bare YAML key. The `build_render_inputs` path guards it (lines 396-400), but a caller constructing `RenderInputs` directly â€” the documented pure-function API â€” can inject arbitrary YAML structure via `role='vision:\\n  injected: evil'`. Same injection class as the iter-1 B1 fix, left open on the pure path.\n\n**Fix:** Add a role whitelist loop in `render_hermes` immediately after the type loop (lines 888-894):\n```python\nfor _aux in inputs.auxiliary_providers:\n    if _aux.role not in AUXILIARY_SLOTS:\n        raise AgentConfigError(f\"Unknown auxiliary role: {_aux.role!r}\")\n```\nPromote `AUXILIARY_SLOTS` to module-level import in render.py (it is currently imported inside `build_render_inputs`).\n\n---\n\n### W2 â€” W-test-ordering-absoluteness NOT fixed\n**Location:** `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:688-742`\n**Raised by:** test-coverage\n\nThe fixture feeds `vision` (index 0) then `web_extract` (index 1) â€” alphabetical AND matching insertion order. An insertion-order-preserving render (no sort at all) emits `['title_generation', 'vision', 'web_extract']` which equals `expected_order`. The test cannot detect a missing sort.\n\n**Fix:** Swap fixture order â€” pass `web_extract` before `vision` in both `aux_specs` and `aux_inputs`. Keep `expected_order = ['title_generation', 'vision', 'web_extract']`. Only a correct sort-by-role implementation passes.\n\n---\n\n### W3 â€” W-test-env-lockstep-multi is self-referential\n**Location:** `tests/test_hermes_multi_provider_templates.py:814-864`\n**Raised by:** test-coverage\n\nSole assertion is `self._emitted_env_keys(legacy_env) == self._emitted_env_keys(canonical_env)`. If both families silently drop `OPENAI_API_KEY` in lockstep, the test stays green.\n\n**Fix:** Pin a literal expected key set before the equality check:\n```python\nexpected_keys = {'ANTHROPIC_API_KEY', 'OPENROUTER_API_KEY', 'OPENAI_API_KEY', 'HERMES_INFERENCE_PROVIDER'}\nassert expected_keys == self._emitted_env_keys(legacy_env)\n# existing equality check stays as lockstep guard\n```\n\n---\n\n### W4 â€” Bedrock dedup legacy path uncovered\n**Location:** `TestLegacyEnvMultiProvider`\n**Raised by:** test-coverage\n\nThe two new bedrock dedup tests target only the canonical (`render_hermes`) path. The legacy template's bedrock dedup logic (`hermes.env.j2` lines 44-65) has no equivalent `bedrock+bedrock` test in `TestLegacyEnvMultiProvider`. There is also no bedrock lockstep analogue to `test_same_type_conflict_warning_in_both_families`.\n\n**Fix:** Add `test_bedrock_dedup_same_creds_no_warning` and `test_bedrock_dedup_diff_creds_emits_warning` to `TestLegacyEnvMultiProvider`.\n\n---\n\n## Suggestions (non-blocking)\n\n| # | Location | Issue | Action |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| S-A | `hermes-env.canonical.j2:35` | `_c.type` uses Jinja2 attribute-fallback on a plain dict; `_c[\"type\"]` is explicit | Low-priority style fix |\n| S-B | `test_unknown_aux_type_raises` fixture | `type=\"zai\"` is in `_BEARER_API_KEY_TYPES` â€” misleading name; use `type=\"perplexity\"` (absent from all sets) or update docstring | Low-priority |\n| S-C | `render.py` | `_HERMES_SUPPORTED_PROVIDERS` and `_AGENT_TYPE_PROVIDER_SUPPORT['hermes']` are identical today; derive one from the other to prevent silent divergence | Low-priority maintenance |\n| S-D | `TestCanonicalMultiProvider.test_explicit_tg_aux_shadows_default:369` | Standalone canonical TG test lacks `assert 'claude-haiku' not in str(tg)` â€” weaker than the lockstep version | Low-priority |\n| S-E | Bedrock same-creds test (canonical) | Only pins `AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID` count; missing `AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY` and `AWS_DEFAULT_REGION` count assertions | Low-priority |\n| S-F | `_build_provider_env_views` | Silent ollama-auxiliary no-op (no env key emitted, no warning) â€” pre-existing, not introduced by #614 | Track as follow-up |\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nW1 (aux-role injection on pure path) is the most material finding â€” same injection class as the B1 fix in iter-1, left open for `RenderInputs` direct callers. W2â€“W4 are test structural weaknesses that leave the ordering contract, the lockstep contract, and the legacy bedrock path untestable against regression. None are blockers for this iteration if the scope is narrowly the e7ceae3..70c09df delta, but W2 and W3 are direct uncorrected carry-overs from iter-2 acceptance criteria.\n\n**Recommended disposition before merge:**\n- W1: Fix (aux-role loop in `render_hermes`) â€” small, same pattern as the type loop just added\n- W2: Fix (swap fixture insertion order) â€” one-line change\n- W3: Fix (pin literal expected_keys) â€” two lines\n- W4: Fix or defer with issue (legacy bedrock dedup tests)\n",
